1 AMEND House Committee Substitute for House Bill No. 2748, Page 1, Section 167.720, Lines
2 2-5, by deleting all of said lines and inserting in lieu thereof the following:
3
4 "(1) "Bilateral coordination", the coordinated use of both sides of the human body,
5 including, but not limited to, crossing the mid-line, and symmetrical, asymmetrical, reciprocal,
6 and sequential movements;
7 (2) "Bone-strengthening activity", physical activity that is primarily designed to increase
8 the strength of specific sites in bones that make up the skeletal system. Bone-strengthening
9 activity produces an impact or tension force on the bones that promotes bone growth and
10 strength;
11 (3) "Moderate physical activity", low- to medium-impact physical exertion designed to
12 increase an individual's heart rate to rise to at least seventy-five percent of his or her maximum
13 heart rate. Activities in this category may include, but are not limited to, running, calisthenics,
14 aerobic exercise, etc.;
15 (4) "Muscle-strengthening activity", physical activity and exercise that increases skeletal
16 muscle strength, power, endurance, and mass;"; and
17
18 Further amend said bill, page, and section, by renumbering all subsequent subdivisions
19 accordingly; and
20
21 Further amend said bill, page, and section, Line 14, by deleting the numbers "2026-27" and
22 inserting in lieu thereof the numbers "2027-28"; and
23
24 Further amend said bill, page, and section, Line 16, by deleting all of said line and inserting in
25 lieu thereof the following:
26
27 "participate in supervised [moderate] physical activity for the"; and
28
29 Further amend said bill and section, Page 2, Line 20, by deleting the word "thirty" and inserting
30 in lieu thereof the words "[thirty] forty"; and
31
32 Further amend said bill, page, and section, Line 23, by inserting after the word "minutes." the
33 following:
34
35 "Such physical activity shall include muscle-strengthening and bone-strengthening activity for
36 no less than an average of eighty minutes per school week for each activity. Such physical
