22 "3. For the purpose of determining whether a student has satisfactorily completed a full
23 course of study each academic year, a school district may elect to designate the time required for
24 physical activity per day, as prescribed in paragraphs (b) and (c) of subdivision (1) of subsection
25 2 of this section, not to exceed ten minutes per day for any one course, subject, or class, toward
